/proc/sys/kernel/kptr_restrict控制内核指针可见性：0=显示给所有人，1=非root用户哈希，2=始终哈希。影响/proc/kallsyms和%pK格式。现代发行版默认为1。与CONFIG_SECURITY_DMESG_RESTRICT结合提供全面地址保护。 Static key (jump label) usage for optimizing security checks:
```c
#include <linux/jump_label.h>

/* Define a static key, initially disabled */
DEFINE_STATIC_KEY_FALSE(security_feature_enabled);

/* In the hot path - near zero cost when disabled */
static inline void check_security(struct task_struct *tsk)
{
    if (static_branch_unlikely(&security_feature_enabled)) {
        /* Expensive security check */
        do_security_audit(tsk);
    }
}

/* Toggle at runtime - patches NOP<->JMP */
static int __init enable_feature(char *str)
{
    static_branch_enable(&security_feature_enabled);
    return 1;
}
__setup("security_audit", enable_feature);
```
When disabled, the check compiles to a NOP (absorbed into pipeline). When enabled, it becomes a JMP to the audit code.

