When memory is hot-added, the buddy allocator must integrate the new pages into its free lists. When memory is hot-removed, pages must be drained from the buddy allocator.

**Hot-add integration:**
```c
// In mm/memory_hotplug.c
int online_pages(unsigned long pfn, unsigned long nr_pages, int nid)
{
    // 1. Initialize struct pages for the new memory
    sparse_add_section(nid, pfn, nr_pages);

    // 2. Add pages to the buddy allocator
    for (page = pfn_to_page(pfn); page < pfn_to_page(pfn + nr_pages); page++) {
        // Set migration type to MIGRATE_MOVABLE by default
        set_pageblock_migratetype(page, MIGRATE_MOVABLE);
        // Add to buddy free lists
        __free_page(page);
    }

    // 3. Update zone statistics
    zone->managed_pages += nr_pages;
    zone->present_pages += nr_pages;

    // 4. Rebuild zonelists
    build_all_zonelists(NULL);

    // 5. Update watermarks
    setup_per_zone_wmarks();
}
```

**Hot-remove draining:**
```c
int offline_pages(unsigned long pfn, unsigned long nr_pages)
{
    // 1. Migrate all movable pages out of the range
    // This is the most time-consuming step
    start_isolate_page_range(pfn, pfn + nr_pages, MIGRATE_MOVABLE);

    // 2. Drain per-CPU page lists
    drain_all_pages(zone);

    // 3. Remove from buddy allocator
    // Pages in buddy free lists are simply removed
    __offline_isolated_pages(pfn, pfn + nr_pages);

    // 4. Update zone statistics
    zone->managed_pages -= nr_pages;

    // 5. Update watermarks
    setup_per_zone_wmarks();
}
```

**Challenges:**
- Unmovable pages (kernel slab, page tables) in the range prevent hot-remove
- ZONE_MOVABLE is designed specifically to enable reliable hot-remove
- Memory compaction may be needed to consolidate movable pages

